h’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":3,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705192,"age":16,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705193,"age":25,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Bertson was born in 1312, in England. She had at least 1 daughter with Henry Lehman. She died in 1365, in her hometown, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1312–1365":"1312–1365","1311–1372":"1311–1372","1338–Female":"1338–Surnud","1338":"1338","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1312":"1312","about 1338":"umbes 1338","1311":"1311","1365":"1365","1453":"1453","1372":"1372","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1312–1365":"1312–1365","1311–1372":"1311–1372","1338–Female":"1338–Kuollut","1338":"1338","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1312":"1312","about 1338":"noin 1338","1311":"1311","1365":"1365","1453":"1453","1372":"1372","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","England":"England","Devon